## 💥 Why does this exist?

If you landed here, you've probably been through the same hell I have.

On the **Pixel 9 Pro XL** (and likely other devices running Android 14/15), tapping the LSPosed notification to open the manager results in an **immediate crash** — no error message, no fallback, nothing. The app just dies.

I tried every available version:
- ✗ Official LSPosed (archived)
- ✗ Community forks
- ✗ Custom builds
- ✗ Different Magisk versions
- ✗ Multiple Zygisk combinations

**Nothing worked.**

The solution? Stop relying on the GUI and do everything the LSPosed Manager app does — directly in SQLite, via shell, with root. That's exactly what this project does.

> **LSPosed Manager CLI** is a fully functional drop-in replacement for the LSPosed Manager app, operating entirely from the command line through direct writes to the framework's SQLite database.

